com.team6133.frc2018.subsystems

Class Drive

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team6133.frc2018.subsystems.Subsystem
      • com.team6133.frc2018.subsystems.Drive

  • public class Drive
extends Subsystem
    This subsystem consists of the robot's drivetrain: 4 CIM motors, 4 talons, and a navXmicro board. The Drive subsystem has several control methods including open loop, heading control, and proximity control. The Drive subsystem also has several methods that handle automatic aiming alignment, autonomous path driving, and manual control.

    Subsystem

      • setOpenLoop

        public void setOpenLoop()
        Open loop control of the robot. Call updateDriveSignal at the start of the teleop periodic loop. This method relies on the mDriveSignal being updated in this way.

      • setTeleopHeadingSetpoint

        public void setTeleopHeadingSetpoint(double heading,
                                     double timeStamp)
        Enable the Heading Setpoint mode in teleop. Specify the heading and the method will prep the PID Controller. The Drive State will change to HEADING_SETPOINT. Call this method once in teleop periodic to initialize the mode, but then call updateTeleopHeadingSetpoint() to allow the driver to update the drive signal.
        Parameters:
        heading - Target heading to use with gyro. Input ranges from -180 to 180.
        timeStamp - The system start time that this method was called.

      • updateTeleopHeadingSetpoint

        public void updateTeleopHeadingSetpoint()
        Updates the PID Heading Control. The driver can still operate in the x and y directions, but this function overrides the twist such that the robot strictly faces left or right. Useful for aiming the robot at a switch or scale.

      • setAlignLaunch

        public void setAlignLaunch(double timeStamp)
        PID Control loop for aligning the drive for shooting. The robot will automatically face left or right (depending on the location of the scale). After a small delay, the robot will also use the proximity sensor to adjust to the GUARD RAIL.
        Parameters:
        timeStamp - The system timestamp when this method was called.

      • updateAlignLaunch

        public void updateAlignLaunch()
        Uses PID sensors to fix the angle w.r.t the scale and the distance w.r.t the GUARD RAIL. There is a small delay before the proximity sensor is used. This is to compensate for the amount of time it takes to orient the sensor facing the GUARD RAIL. Call this method in teleop periodic after the initial call to setAlignLaunch()
        See Also:
        setAlignLaunch(double)

      • setPolarDrive

        public void setPolarDrive(double heading,
                          double timeStamp)
        Configure the robot for Polar Drive. Not likely to be used, but written for testing purposes.
        Parameters:
        heading - The target heading. Input ranges from -180 to 180.
        timeStamp - The system time that this method was called.
